Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Bring back to the boil. Cook until @linguine{180%g} is tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{120%g}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Halve the asparagus widthways.

Once the mushrooms and bacon are golden, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

When the pasta has 3 mins left, add the asparagus to the same pan and cook for the remaining time.

Once the pasta and asparagus are cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to prevent it sticking.

Stir the @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the mushrooms and bacon, simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked pasta, asparagus and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to the sauce and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the bacon and mushroom linguine between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!